00:48:09,000 --> 00:48:12,000
Let's talk about some player power changes based on PTR feedback.

278
00:48:12,000 --> 00:48:18,000
So I want to start by framing our goals for Torment difficulties.

279
00:48:19,000 --> 00:48:23,000
So Torment 1, we want all content to be available in the game.

280
00:48:23,000 --> 00:48:24,000
You can fight Lilith.

281
00:48:24,000 --> 00:48:25,000
You can fight the Boss Latter.

282
00:48:25,000 --> 00:48:27,000
You can go to the Dark Citadel, you know, et cetera.

283
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:28,000
All these activities are available.

284
00:48:29,000 --> 00:48:32,000
Torment 4 is intended to be aspirational content.

285
00:48:32,000 --> 00:48:36,000
And what that means is you've already unlocked everything in the game when you enter Torment 1.

286
00:48:36,000 --> 00:48:45,000
But Torment 4 is like the essence of Diablo, like build crafting, where you're just pushing your character as far as you can go.

287
00:48:45,000 --> 00:48:51,000
And Torment 4 exists for that purpose, for people who want to push their character as far as they can go.

288
00:48:51,000 --> 00:49:00,000
And with that said, and the reason why I'm saying this is because we were seeing that people were getting to Torment 4 way faster and way easier than we were hoping for in the PTR.

289
00:49:00,000 --> 00:49:04,000
And, you know, which is just another great, like, it's great that we did the PTR because we saw that.

290
00:49:05,000 --> 00:49:13,000
And with that all said, we've made some changes to kind of keep Torment 4 this, you know, really challenging and exciting thing to reach.

291
00:49:15,000 --> 00:49:21,000
We've reverted the skill damage bonus from main stat back to what it was in Season 5.

292
00:49:21,000 --> 00:49:25,000
So we had actually doubled it in the PTR, but we found that that was just giving players too much power.

293
00:49:25,000 --> 00:49:26,000
Too much.

294
00:49:26,000 --> 00:49:27,000
So we sent it back.

295
00:49:28,000 --> 00:49:31,000
And we also pulled back on Legendary Glyph power a bit.

296
00:49:31,000 --> 00:49:32,000
Colin, do you want to talk about that?

297
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:40,000
Yeah, so we reduced the scaling on the glyphs quite a bit because we found that it was really devaluing a lot of the aspect rolls or rolls on your gear.

298
00:49:40,000 --> 00:49:48,000
Like when you're getting 2,000 additive damage from a glyph, it's really hard to actually feel anything on your gear through tempering or through those affects that are dropping.

299
00:49:48,000 --> 00:49:51,000
So essentially what we've done is pair that back.

300
00:49:51,000 --> 00:49:52,000
We've redistributed it.

301
00:49:52,000 --> 00:49:54,000
We'll cover that a little bit on where we put some of that power.

302
00:49:55,000 --> 00:49:56,000
But overall, we think this feels a lot better.

303
00:49:56,000 --> 00:50:00,000
Glyphs aren't just carrying, like, 80% of your power on a build.

304
00:50:00,000 --> 00:50:07,000
And it just feels a lot better so that it doesn't feel as sort of mandatory that I have to get all five glyphs and level them up to actually be pushing.

305
00:50:07,000 --> 00:50:13,000
It's a lot more about what are the aspects you have, what are the uniques you have, what are the nodes you're actually getting on the Paragon board.

306
00:50:13,000 --> 00:50:14,000
I think it feels a lot better.

307
00:50:15,000 --> 00:50:21,000
Yeah, and, like, I think one of the important things to say about this is that, like, it's really awesome to get a tremendous amount of power from one source.

308
00:50:21,000 --> 00:50:30,000
But because there are so many different sources of power in the game, if one source gives too much power, it makes the other sources feel kind of unimportant.

309
00:50:30,000 --> 00:50:32,000
And that's not fun.

310
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:37,000
So we want to make sure that every source of power in the game is contributing to your build in very meaningful ways.

311
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:41,000
And so this change is helping other sources of power feel really punchy.

312
00:50:41,000 --> 00:50:42,000
Definitely.

313
00:50:42,000 --> 00:50:42,000
Yeah.

314
00:50:44,000 --> 00:50:44,000
Awesome.

315
00:50:44,000 --> 00:50:51,000
I know tons of changes here with player power, tons of changes with, like, progression, including difficulty.

316
00:50:51,000 --> 00:50:52,000
And itemization.

317
00:50:54,000 --> 00:50:56,000
Do we have anything else on progression?

318
00:50:57,000 --> 00:51:01,000
I think one thing I think that's really important to touch on is the torment goals here, right?

319
00:51:01,000 --> 00:51:01,000
Yeah.

320
00:51:01,000 --> 00:51:13,000
Because it's a definite fundamental shift from Season 5 in that you think about World Tier 3 into World Tier 4, and you're sort of racing to get to World Tier 4 as fast as possible because that's where all the best items can drop.

321
00:51:13,000 --> 00:51:13,000
Yeah.

322
00:51:13,000 --> 00:51:17,000
And we've sort of just changed that to Torment 1 is where all the best items can drop.

323
00:51:17,000 --> 00:51:18,000
It's where everything unlocks.

324
00:51:18,000 --> 00:51:23,000
But essentially, Torment 2, 3, and 4 increase the odds of those things happening.

325
00:51:23,000 --> 00:51:24,000
So it's just efficiency, right?

326
00:51:24,000 --> 00:51:25,000
Yeah.

327
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:34,000
We don't necessarily want to say you must get to Torment 4 to experience the game or to get the best drops in the game, similar to World Tier 4 in Season 5.

328
00:51:34,000 --> 00:51:35,000
It's a very different feeling.

329
00:51:35,000 --> 00:51:40,000
So we're excited to see how that plays out, and we want to sort of see what you all think as well.

330
00:51:41,000 --> 00:51:41,000
Yeah.

331
00:51:41,000 --> 00:51:46,000
And just to reiterate, you know, all of the content, all of the best gear can be found in Torment 1.

332
00:51:46,000 --> 00:51:49,000
So if that's where your build feels most comfortable farming, that's great.

333
00:51:50,000 --> 00:51:51,000
You can still achieve all your goals.

334
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:53,000
You can really max out your character there.

335
00:51:53,000 --> 00:51:58,000
It just, you get a reward for pushing this harder difficulty by more efficiency.

336
00:51:58,000 --> 00:51:58,000
Yeah.

337
00:51:59,000 --> 00:52:04,000
And that's like what affords Torment 4 the means to, or like the space to be really hard.

338
00:52:04,000 --> 00:52:04,000
Definitely.

339
00:52:04,000 --> 00:52:06,000
It's because you don't have to get there.

